parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause internal engine damage, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: the timing chain makes a rattling or dreadful noise

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Cradle Failure Leading to Control Arm Breakage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the engine cradle can cause the control arm to break, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially fatal consequences, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected loss of steering control
vehicle comes to a grinding halt
tire rotates inward and back into the fender well

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Left Rear Brake Light Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the left rear brake light can cause confusion to other drivers, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses, as they may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions to slow down or stop.
symptoms: The left rear brake light works sporadically
the brake light fails to illuminate consistently
the brake light flickers on and off
replacing the bulb only temporarily corrects the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition control module can cause the engine to run rough, stall, or shut off, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle has a rough idle
the vehicle experiences a loss of power.
